SAA spokesperson Tlali Tlali speaks to eNCA. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) will reinstate international flights services from OR Tambo International Airport on Sunday. SAA spokesperson Tlali Tlali says other flights from international stations will only start operating from Monday. WATCH: SAA cancels all flights after strike call Domestic flights will remain cancelled on Sunday and Monday. "Domestic flight passengers will continue to be re-accommodated as domestic flights will remain cancelled." The strike at SAA  got underway on Friday, as workers demand higher wages and the scrapping of a plan to retrench hundreds of employees. Watch the full interview with SAA spokesperson Tlali Tlali in the above video for more.